@database "MOSNet.guide"

@node main "MOSNet - Table of contents"

 Welcome to MOSNet - a free portable TCP/IP stack for Amiga family of operating systems.

 The amount of information is huge so this documentation is incomplete and is under constant
development. Please @{"let the authors know" link support} what needs to be documented first.
An active help in documentation development is appreciated.

 Table of contents:

 @{"Introduction" link introduction}
 @{"System requirements" link requirements}
 @{"Distribution" link distribution}
 @{"Installation" link installation}
 @{"Configuration" link configuration}
 @{"FAQ" link faq}
 @{"Version history" link history}
 @{"Future" link future}
 @{"Support" link support}
 @{"Thanks" link thanks}

@endnode
@node introduction Introduction

 MOSNet is a free portable implementation of a TCP/IP stack for Amiga family of operating
systems.

 Current features of MOSNet are:

 - Support for IPv4 protocol;
 - Binary-level software compatibility with Miami TCP stack (incomplete);
 - Ability to use MiamiDeluxe graphical control panels;
 - Compact, modular design;
 - T/TCP protocol support;
 - Source-level software compatibility with Roadshow TCP stack (incomplete);
 - Extremely flexible configuration mechanism;
 - ARexx support;
 - Command shell-level compatibility with BSD family of operating systems.
 - Easy portability accross all Amiga-alike operating systems.

@endnode
@node requirements "System requirements"

 The only supported operating system at the moment is MorphOS. MOSNet is developed and tested
on MorphOS v1.4.5. The kernel and libraries need no additional components to work.

 MUI.MiamiPanel requires the following third party MUI custom classes to be
installed in your system:

 - BWin.mcc
 - Lamp.mcc
 - TheBar.mcc
 - Urltext.mcc

 These classes are included in the MOSNet distribution package.

@endnode
